**SF5-104 complete.** Here's a summary of everything delivered:

## What was built

### `Inspector.tsx` — Multi-Select Inspector
- **`MixedNumericInput`** component: shows `—` placeholder when selected items have different values; committing a value applies to ALL selected items via dispatch loop
- **`getMixedValue<T>()`** helper: returns shared value or `null` (mixed) for any property
- **Multi-select section** (renders when 2+ items selected):
  - Count display ("3 items")
  - Batch-editable X/Y position fields with mixed-value indicators
  - 4 **Nudge** arrow buttons (←→↑↓) dispatching `item:move` with ±10px
  - **Duplicate Selected** — dispatches `item:add` per item with +20/+20 offset
  - **Delete Selected** — dispatches `item:delete` per item

### `Toolbar.tsx` — Keyboard Shortcuts
- Reads live store state inside the event handler (no stale closures)
- `Delete/Backspace` → delete selected items
- `Ctrl+D` → duplicate selected items  
- `Ctrl+A` → select all items on active layer
- `Arrow keys` → nudge ±1px; `Shift+Arrow` → nudge ±10px
- `Escape` → clear selection
- Contextual selection toolbar with Duplicate/Delete buttons + `<kbd>` shortcut hints

### `workspace.css` — New Styles
Mixed-value input styling, nudge grid/buttons, multi-select action layout, shortcut hint badges, selection info chip, toolbar danger button variant

### `Inspector.test.tsx` — 13 Tests
Empty state, single item, multi-select count, mixed X placeholder, uniform X value, delete dispatches for all, duplicate creates copies, nudge up/down/left/right, duplicate offset verification

**Results:** 13/13 tests ✅ · Full build ✅